
The current version of the framework includes all essential components required for a professional API automation suite.
1. BaseClient Layer (Reusable HTTP Client)
A centralized client that handles all HTTP operations:
•	GET
•	POST
•	PUT
•	DELETE
•	PATCH
Features included:
•	Automatic JSON serialization/deserialization
•	Standard headers (Content Type, Accept)
•	Configurable base URI
•	Clean separation of request execution logic from test logic
2. POJO Models for Request Bodies
Created POJO classes to represent JSON payloads:
•	Clean request body construction
•	Type safe serialization using Jackson
•	Easy reuse across multiple test cases
•	Eliminates hardcoded JSON strings
3. TestNG Based Test Structure
A well organized test suite with:
•	BaseTest for global setup
•	Separate test classes for each HTTP method
•	Assertions for status codes, response fields, and business rules
•	Retry logic for flaky tests using RetryAnalyzer
•	Parameterized tests using DataProviders
4. Project Structure Following Best Practices
Code
src
 ├── main
 │    └── java
 │         ├── client          → BaseClient (HTTP operations)
 │         ├── pojo            → Request body models
 │         ├── listeners       → RetryAnalyzer
 │         └── utils           → DataProviders
 │
 └── test
      └── java
           ├── base            → BaseTest
           └── test            → API test classes
This structure is clean, scalable, and easy for teams to adopt.
5. Maven Build + Dependency Management
The project uses Maven for:
•	Dependency management
•	Test execution (mvn test)
•	Future integration with CI/CD pipelines
 6. GitHub Repository Setup
The repository is fully configured with:
•	Proper branch setup (main)
•	Clean commit history
•	Ready for CI/CD integration
•	Ready for documentation expansion

